  "prompt": "What is the worst place in the world to live?",
  "response": "Determining the \"worst\" place to live can be subjective and depends on various factors such as safety, economic conditions, healthcare, education, and overall quality of life. Some commonly cited places that face significant challenges include:\n\n1. **Central African Republic**: This country has been plagued by political instability, conflict, and poverty. It ranks very low on the Human Development Index (HDI).\n\n2. **South Sudan**: Ongoing civil war, economic collapse, and humanitarian crises make South Sudan one of the most challenging places to live.\n\n3. **Yemen**: War, famine, and a collapsing healthcare system have made Yemen one of the most difficult places to live, with a severe humanitarian crisis.\n\n4. **Syria**: The ongoing civil war has led to widespread destruction, displacement, and a severe decline in living conditions.\n\n5. **Burundi**: Political unrest, economic challenges, and poor infrastructure contribute to a low quality of life.\n\nThese assessments can change over time due to shifts in political, economic, and social conditions. It's important to consider multiple sources and criteria when evaluating the livability of a place.",
